\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 YOUR TASKS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 1. User Assumption Audit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Identify what the product assumes about users:\
Ask:\uc0\u8232 \'95 What knowledge is assumed?\u8232 \'95 What motivation is assumed?\u8232 \'95 What emotional state is assumed?\u8232 \'95 What time, energy, or confidence is assumed?\
Surface:\uc0\u8232 \'95 Where users may be more anxious, tired, or overwhelmed\u8232 \'95 Where users may be less skilled than expected\u8232 \'95 Where users may behave \'93irrationally\'94 but predictably\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 2. Builder Bias Audit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Identify where the builder\'92s strengths may distort the product:\
Ask:\uc0\u8232 \'95 Where is expert thinking leaking into beginner UX?\u8232 \'95 Where is builder speed mistaken for user readiness?\u8232 \'95 Where does personal workflow masquerade as universal workflow?\
Surface:\uc0\u8232 \'95 Places optimized for how the builder thinks, not users\u8232 \'95 Features that feel elegant to build but awkward to use\u8232 \'95 Over-automation or under-automation driven by preference\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 3. Success Definition Audit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Challenge the definition of \'93working\'94:\
Ask:\uc0\u8232 \'95 What does the builder consider success?\u8232 \'95 What would users consider success?\u8232 \'95 Where do those definitions diverge?\
Surface:\uc0\u8232 \'95 Metrics that look good but don\'92t feel good\u8232 \'95 Success states that lack emotional payoff\u8232 \'95 Wins that are invisible to users\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 4. Risk & Avoidance Audit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Look for emotional avoidance:\
Ask:\uc0\u8232 \'95 What problems is the product carefully not solving?\u8232 \'95 Where is complexity avoided instead of managed?\u8232 \'95 Where is control withheld out of fear?\
Surface:\uc0\u8232 \'95 Hard problems deferred indefinitely\u8232 \'95 Features made optional to avoid accountability\u8232 \'95 Safety rails that are really fear rails\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 5. Narrative Blind Spot Audit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Evaluate the story the product tells:\
Ask:\uc0\u8232 \'95 What story does the builder think this product tells?\u8232 \'95 What story does it actually tell through behavior?\u8232 \'95 Where does the story fracture?\
Surface:\uc0\u8232 \'95 Mixed messaging\u8232 \'95 Implied promises not fulfilled\u8232 \'95 Places where trust could erode quietly\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 OUTPUT FORMAT\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Return findings grouped by 
\f1\b Blind Spot Theme
\f0\b0 .\
For each include:\uc0\u8232 \'95 The assumption or bias\u8232 \'95 Evidence of its presence\u8232 \'95 How it shapes the product today\u8232 \'95 The risk it introduces\u8232 \'95 A reframing or corrective action\
End with:\uc0\u8232 \'95 The single most dangerous blind spot\u8232 \'95 The single most underutilized strength of the builder\u8232 \'95 One strategic question the builder should sit with before the next build cycle\
Your mandate:\uc0\u8232 Not comfort.\u8232 Clarity.\
